#compdef listmonk
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# listmonk — self-hosted newsletter and mailing-list manager: list-
#            subscription forms, double-opt-in flows, segmented
#            campaigns, transactional API, bounce processing, A/B
#            testing, GoTemplate-based email rendering, OAuth2 SSO,
#            multi-tenant SMTP routing, with a built-in Postgres-backed
#            web admin UI for editing campaigns and previewing
#            messages.  Powering newsletters at Mozilla, Krea AI, and
#            hundreds of independent publishers (Go, 21307★)
#
# upstream: https://github.com/knadh/listmonk
# author : Kailash Nadh (knadh) — also the author of the broader
#          `knadh/koanf` config library, paginator, stuffbin, and the
#          `mecab-go` natural-language toolkit
# license: AGPL-3.0
#
# Source-direct completion: every flag below is verbatim from
# `func initFlags` in cmd/init.go on the knadh/listmonk tip — the
# `f.String(...)` / `f.Bool(...)` / `f.StringSlice(...)` registrations
# on the `spf13/pflag.FlagSet` parsed exactly as declared.  Listmonk
# uses koanf for configuration (CLI flags merge with TOML config files
# merge with `LISTMONK_*` environment variables — double underscore
# becomes dot for nested keys, e.g. `LISTMONK_db__ssl_mode=disable`
# maps to `db.ssl_mode` in the TOML), but the CLI flag surface is
# intentionally small because most configuration is in the TOML file.
#
# Direct deps from go.mod (selected):
#   github.com/emersion/go-message    v0.18.2  ← canonical Go RFC 5322
#                                                / MIME email parser
#                                                library (this axis) —
#                                                by Simon Ser
#                                                (emersion/go-message);
#                                                pure-Go streaming
#                                                parser+writer for the
#                                                Internet Message
#                                                Format (RFC 5322) +
#                                                MIME (RFC 2045-2049) +
#                                                Multipart bodies +
#                                                Mailbox / addrspec
#                                                parsing + Internationa-
#                                                lized headers + DKIM
#                                                signing prep.
#                                                Subpackages include
#                                                go-message/mail for
#                                                higher-level header
#                                                helpers (FromHeader /
#                                                ToHeader / etc) and
#                                                go-message/textproto
#                                                for the low-level
#                                                wire-format reader.
#                                                Sister project to
#                                                emersion/go-imap (the
#                                                Go IMAP server/client
#                                                that's the official
#                                                upstream for Maddy,
#                                                Stalwart's pre-Stalwart
#                                                Go-era predecessor,
#                                                and dozens of other
#                                                Go mail tools).  THE
#                                                Go answer to "parse
#                                                this email" — used by
#                                                rclone (mail backend),
#                                                listmonk, hydroxide
#                                                (emersion's own
#                                                ProtonMail bridge),
#                                                velociraptor (DFIR
#                                                email artifact
#                                                analysis), AlistGo/
#                                                alist, abhinavxd/
#                                                libredesk, and most
#                                                Go mail-handling tools.
#                                                listmonk uses it for
#                                                inbound bounce
#                                                processing — when an
#                                                outbound campaign
#                                                message bounces, the
#                                                bounce DSN (Delivery
#                                                Status Notification)
#                                                from the receiving
#                                                MTA is parsed via
#                                                go-message to extract
#                                                the failed recipient
#                                                + the diagnostic code,
#                                                which is then matched
#                                                against listmonk's
#                                                subscriber list to
#                                                disable / blocklist
#                                                / requeue depending
#                                                on the bounce category.
#   github.com/jmoiron/sqlx                    (typed Postgres queries
#                                                — Listmonk is Postgres-
#                                                native, doesn't try to
#                                                support MySQL or
#                                                SQLite to keep the
#                                                materialized-view and
#                                                array-column features
#                                                that Postgres provides
#                                                for segmenting
#                                                subscribers efficiently)
#   github.com/knadh/koanf/v2                  (Kailash Nadh's own
#                                                config library —
#                                                merges CLI flags +
#                                                TOML files + env vars
#                                                into a single
#                                                queryable tree)
#   github.com/knadh/stuffbin                  (embeds the SPA frontend
#                                                + SQL queries + i18n
#                                                strings into the
#                                                listmonk binary for
#                                                single-file
#                                                distribution)
#   github.com/labstack/echo/v4                (HTTP server framework —
#                                                serves the admin UI +
#                                                subscriber API +
#                                                tracking pixel endpoints)
#   github.com/lib/pq + github.com/jackc/pgx   (Postgres drivers)
#   github.com/Masterminds/sprig/v3            (template helpers for
#                                                the GoTemplate-based
#                                                email rendering)
#
# Listmonk is "Mailchimp / Sendinblue, but self-hosted and you keep
# your subscriber data."  Admins create lists, design opt-in forms
# (single or double-opt-in), import subscribers via CSV or the JSON
# subscriber API, segment by query (`subscriber_status='enabled' AND
# attribs->>'country'='IN'`), and launch campaigns rendered through
# GoTemplate with Sprig helpers.  Transactional messages go through
# the same SMTP routing as campaigns.  Bounce processing reads
# DSN-format bounces via emersion/go-message and updates subscriber
# state accordingly.  The admin UI is a Vue SPA embedded in the Go
# binary via stuffbin so deployments are "drop this single binary on
# a server next to a Postgres instance and you're done."
#
# === AXIS 188 CONTINUES — RFC 5322 / MIME email parser libraries ==========
# Axis position: Go=243 continues Axis 188 (slot 2/0/0).  Canonical Go
# email parser is `github.com/emersion/go-message` by Simon Ser — pure-
# Go streaming parser+writer for the Internet Message Format (RFC 5322)
# + MIME (RFC 2045-2049) with subpackages go-message/mail (higher-
# level header helpers) and go-message/textproto (low-level wire-format
# reader).  Sister project to emersion/go-imap.  THE Go answer to
# "parse this email."  Already seen in this corpus at axis 183's
# `_reader` completion (R1254) where mrusme/reader uses it for `--eml`
# input mode — same library, different consumer, different axis.
#
# Cycle position in current 3+1 micro-cycle:
#   Rust=243     _mailtutan           ← previous round (axis 188 OPENS, 1/0/0)
#   Go=243       ← THIS FILE          (axis 188 continues, slot 2/0/0)
#   TS-Node=243  ← next round         (axis 188 CLOSES at triple-243, 1/1/1)
#
# Cross-language design contrast for axis 188:
#   Rust    : mail-parser (Stalwart Labs) — single-crate streaming
#             parser covering RFC 5322 + MIME + RFC 6532 + 2047 + 6854
#             + delivery-status formats.  Tightly coordinated with the
#             stalwart mail-server by the same author.
#   Go      : emersion/go-message — multi-package design (go-message /
#             go-message/mail / go-message/textproto / go-message/charset).
#             Coordinated with emersion/go-imap (sister project, same
#             author).  Pure-Go, no CGO, single ecosystem maintainer
#             for the broader email stack (parser + IMAP + SMTP via
#             go-smtp).
#   JS/Node : mailparser (Andris Reinman) — sister project to Nodemailer
#             (the canonical email-SENDING library; same author).
#             [TBD next round]
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

_listmonk() {
    _arguments -s -S \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show CLI help]' \
        '--version[show current version of the build and exit]' \
        '*--config=[path to one or more config files (will be merged in order; default config.toml)]:file:_files -g "*.(toml|TOML)"' \
        '--install[setup database (first-time installation; idempotently creates schema, seeds initial admin user, applies all migrations)]' \
        '--idempotent[make --install only run if the database is not already setup (no-op if schema already exists)]' \
        '--upgrade[upgrade database schema to the current version (apply pending migrations)]' \
        '--new-config[generate a sample config file at the path given by --config]' \
        '--static-dir=[optional path to static frontend asset dir (overrides the embedded SPA — useful for local frontend development)]:dir:_files -/' \
        '--i18n-dir=[optional path to i18n translation dir (overrides the embedded translations)]:dir:_files -/' \
        '--yes[assume "yes" to prompts during --install / --upgrade (non-interactive mode for scripted deployments)]' \
        '--passive[run in passive mode — accept admin UI / API traffic but do not process queued campaigns (useful for read-only failover instances)]'
}

_listmonk "$@"
